The Just Transition Mechanism, a part of the overall sustainable investment plan, will provide targeted support for regions that will require a bigger transition effort over the period 2021-2027, to alleviate the socio-economic impact of the transition.**************It will consist of three main sources of financing: the fund itself, which will receive €7.5 billion of fresh EU funds in the EU’s next long-term budget; a dedicated just transition scheme under the InvestEU program to mobilize up to €45 billion of investments; and a public sector loan facility with the European Investment Bank backed by the EU budget to mobilise between €25 and €30 billion of investments.**************This mechanism has been set up with €5 billion in EU funding and it is also backed by an additional amount from other sources like national funds or European Investment Bank’s private sector loan facility “Enabling Europe: A new deal on climate change – supporting economic transformation through clean energy investments worth more than 1 trillion euro across all 28 countries; this financing package was approved last year but we have no idea how these loans would be**************377**************0.7122508883476257**************0
